Core Strategies
Terraform Native (preferred for IaC-first teams)
Use terraform plan -detailed-exitcode in your CI/CD pipeline against the current state and cloud provider.
Exit codes: 0 â†’ no drift,,, 2 â†’ drift detected (resources differ)
Automate this as a scheduled job per environment (e.g., nightly).

AWS CloudFormation Drift Detection
If some stacks are CloudFormation-based, run aws cloudformation detect-stack-drift and track results in CloudWatch or EventBridge.
Integrate alerts when drift status != IN_SYNC.

Cross-environment Baseline Comparison
Store your desired state (Terraform plans or manifests) in a central repo.
Periodically re-apply plans against each environment, but with plan only â€” not apply.
Differences highlight environment-specific drifts.

Policy & Guardrails
Use AWS Config or OPA/Conftest to continuously evaluate if resources match desired configurations.
Example: ensure all S3 buckets are encrypted or IAM roles donâ€™t have wildcard permissions.

Observability-Driven Drift Alerts
Feed drift detection logs/events into CloudWatch, Prometheus, or ELK.
Create alerts (Slack/Teams/Email) so drift doesnâ€™t remain invisible.

ðŸš€ Best Practices
Shift left: Run drift checks in lower environments (staging, QA) before promoting infra changes to prod.
Non-blocking mode: At first, only alert on drift; later, enforce block/rollback policies.
Version everything: Keep Terraform state files and module versions pinned across environments.
Auto-remediation (careful in prod): Optionally trigger a controlled terraform apply in staging/QA to auto-fix drift, but keep prod remediation manual + approved.

âš¡ Example: Nightly drift check job for Terraform in GitHub Actions
name: Drift Detection
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 2 * * *" # run daily at 2am UTC
jobs:
  drift-check:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - name: Setup Terraform
        uses: hashicorp/setup-terraform@v2
      - name: Terraform Init
        run: terraform init
      - name: Terraform Plan (drift detection)
        run: terraform plan -detailed-exitcode || echo "Drift detected!"